A 27-year-old man has been transported to hospital after getting into serious difficulties in the water at North Beach in Durban on Sunday morning.ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
ER24 spokesperson Annine Siddall said at approximately 9.45am, paramedics had been called by life guards to transport the man to Addington Hospital for further medical care.
"The man had already been stabilised by life guards."
She said: "The exact circumstances surrounding the incident are not yet known to our paramedics but local authorities were on the scene."
READ: Six-year-old drowns on KZN North Coast
Last month, an eight-year-old boy drowned on the KwaZulu-Natal South Coast.
Netcare911 spokesman Nick Dollman said in a statement at the time that paramedics had responded to reports of a drowning at the Southbroom Main Beach.
“Reports from the scene allege that the victim was swimming in the lagoon with two other boys when the incident occurred.
The two boys called for help when they noticed their friend was in trouble.” 
